This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with feature learning in convolutional neural networks for image recognition tasks. It also incorporates a transformation invariant pooling operator to handle nuisance variations in the data, which is a common problem in computer vision. 

It is also likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories as it involves the use of deep neural networks for feature learning and classification tasks. 

The Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category is also a possibility as the paper discusses the use of siamese architectures for handling transformations in the data. 

Finally, the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category is a possibility as the paper deals with image recognition tasks and the use of convolutional neural networks for feature learning.
